  "text": "For tissue characterization (n = 8), the heart section of interest was trimmed and shaped to obtain a parallelepiped of 10 × 30 × 5 mm 3 in line with previously published studies [CITATION_1] . Specific shape was designed to get proper tissular gripping and ensure that rupture would occur in the center of the sample and not beside the clamps.",
